This paper deals with data stream algorithms, which are typically studied in the computer science subfield of data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves analysis of algorithms and information theory (cs.IT), as well as machine learning and statistics (cs.LG). The problems studied in the paper, such as heavy hitters and inner product estimation, are common in data mining (cs.DM). Finally, the paper proposes a new model for data streams, which could be considered a subfield of streaming algorithms (cs.SI).
